(2) 鄭匡佑(2004)。探討人體動作之新觀點—動態系統。成大體育37(4), 8-13。
(3) Cheng, K.B. and Hubbard, M. (2005) Optimal compliant-surface jumping: a multi-segment model of springboard standing jumps. Journal of Biomechanics 38, 1822-1829. (SCI 2007 Engineering Biomedical 6/44, impact factor 2.897)
(4) Cheng, K.B. and Chen, W.C. (2005). Optimal standing long jumping simulation from different starting postures. Journal of Mechanics in Medicine and Biology 5, 203-215. (SCI)
(5) 鄭匡佑(2005)。電腦模擬在運動生物力學的應用。科學月刊 36 (3), 236-239。
(6) 鄭匡佑(2005)。太極拳之生物力學相關研究近況。成大體育38(2), 14-17。
(7) Hubbard, M. and Cheng, K.B. (2007). Optimal discus trajectories. Journal of Biomechanics 40, 3650-3659. (SCI 2006 Engineering Biomedical 8/42, impact factor 2.542)
(8) Cheng, K.B. and Hubbard, M. (2008). Role of arms in somersaulting from compliant surfaces: a simulation study of springboard standing dives. Human Movement Science 27, 80-95. (SCI 2007 Sport Sciences 35/72, SSCI Psychology 46/60, impact factor 1.252)
(9) Cheng, K.B., Wang, C.H., Chen, H.C., Wu, C.D, and Chiu, H.T. (2008). The mechanisms that enable arm motion to enhance vertical jump performance—A simulation study. Journal of Biomechanics 41 (9), 1847-54. (SCI 2007 Engineering Biomedical 6/44, impact factor 2.897)
(10) Cheng, K.B. (2008). The relationship between joint strength and standing vertical jump performance. Journal of Applied Biomechanics 24, 224-233. (SCI 2007 Sport Sciences 38/72, impact factor 1.123)
(11) Yao-Yang Tsai, Wen-Chieh Lin, Kuangyou B. Cheng, Jehee Lee, Tong-Yee Lee (2010). Real-time Physics-based 3D Biped Character Animation Using an Inverted Pendulum Model. IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics, 16(2), 325-337. (SCI/EI)
(12) Chiu, H.T., Wang, C.H. and Cheng, K.B. (2010) The three-dimensional kinematics of a barbell during the snatch of Taiwanese weightlifters. Journal of Strength and Conditioning Research, 24(6), 1520-1526.(SCI)
(13) Hirokazu KIUCHI, Motomu NAKASHIMA, Kuangyou B. CHENG, Mont HUBBARD (2010). Modeling Fluid Forces in the Dive Start of Competitive Swimming, Journal of Biomechanical Science and Engineering 5, 314-328.
(14) Chen, H-C, Cheng, K.B., Liu, Y-J, Chiu, H-T, Cheng, K-Y (2010). The Defence Technique of Tai Chi Push Hands – A Case Study. Journal of Sports Sciences, 28: 14, 1595-1604. (SCI)
(15) Sung, Y-H, Cheng, K.B., Cheng, K.Y., Chen, Y-R (2011). 新傳媒時代的快速走紅現象分析。《中大管理研究》第6 捲, 132-145。
 
